records.nl_statement: Let $p$ and $q$ be distinct odd primes such that $p-1$ divides $q-1$. If $(n, p q)=1$, show that $n^{q-1} \equiv 1(p q)$.

  (hn : n.gcd (p*q) = 1) :

records.nl_statement:
Let $f$ be a real function on the real line with continuous third derivative. Prove that there exists a point $a$ such that
$f(a) \cdot f^{\prime}(a) \cdot f^{\prime \prime}(a) \cdot f^{\prime \prime \prime}(a) \geq 0$.
